* What are we trying to achieve when we build a system?
    1- Reliable: ability of a system to perform its intended functions correctly and consistently over time, even under expected or stressful conditions.
    2- Scalable: ability to deal with heavy traffic and adapt with the high traffic.
    3- Maintainability: Ability to add new features, edit existing features without facing any complexity.

* Types of Scaling
    1- Scaling Up(Vertical Scaling).
    2- Scaling Out (Horizontal).



